00:00:21.623 --> 00:00:23.925 position:19% line:83% align:start
[HELM] Guess that's all
that's worth anything, huh?

00:00:24.057 --> 00:00:26.561 position:16% line:83% align:start
Yeah, it was pretty slim
pickings, sir.

00:00:26.694 --> 00:00:29.062 position:19% line:83% align:start
That ain't enough food
for us all.

00:00:29.196 --> 00:00:30.598 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Helm scoffs]

00:00:30.732 --> 00:00:34.101 position:5% line:83% align:start
We'll have to see what Morteln's
got that we can plunder.

00:00:35.937 --> 00:00:40.340 position:21% line:89% align:start
[indistinct chatter]

00:00:41.843 --> 00:00:44.411 position:5% line:83% align:start
Make sure you drive those stakes
in nice and deep!

00:00:44.546 --> 00:00:46.113 position:27% line:83% align:start
-[VILLAGERS] Sir!
-Boss.

00:00:46.413 --> 00:00:48.683 position:33% line:83% align:start
I'm guessing
you don't have good news, huh?

00:00:48.816 --> 00:00:51.451 position:7% line:83% align:start
A village in the knight's fief
of Liptaver's gone.

00:00:51.586 --> 00:00:53.021 position:13% line:89% align:start
It was attacked by bandits.

00:00:53.153 --> 00:00:54.889 position:24% line:83% align:start
They burned it all
to the ground.

00:00:55.690 --> 00:00:58.125 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's only been three weeks
since we returned.

00:00:58.258 --> 00:01:00.327 position:19% line:83% align:start
They've already made it
that far?

00:01:00.460 --> 00:01:02.730 position:16% line:83% align:start
So then, they'll get here
before the two-month deadline

00:01:02.864 --> 00:01:04.131 position:21% line:89% align:start
we were planning on.

00:01:04.264 --> 00:01:05.800 position:38% line:83% align:start
[FEUILLE]
Yeah, you're right about that.

00:01:05.934 --> 00:01:08.168 position:38% line:83% align:start
Hey, Pas,
I need you to get the word out.

00:01:08.670 --> 00:01:11.371 position:7% line:83% align:start
Tell the leader of each village
to hurry here now.

00:01:11.506 --> 00:01:12.507 position:44% line:89% align:start
Sir!

00:01:12.640 --> 00:01:13.975 position:30% line:83% align:start
Make sure that
Cointreau and Glacage

00:01:14.107 --> 00:01:15.777 position:7% line:89% align:start
know they are to come as well.

00:01:15.910 --> 00:01:17.144 position:27% line:89% align:start
Understood, sir.

00:01:17.812 --> 00:01:19.647 position:27% line:83% align:start
[PAS] The bandits
will be getting here sooner

00:01:19.781 --> 00:01:20.548 position:27% line:89% align:start
than we thought.

00:01:20.682 --> 00:01:23.017 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'll stop them! I have a dream

00:01:23.150 --> 00:01:25.252 position:21% line:83% align:start
and that's to create
a land of sweets.

00:01:25.385 --> 00:01:28.690 position:5% line:83% align:start
I can't let some tasteless jerks
destroy it!

00:01:30.858 --> 00:01:33.427 position:13% line:83% align:start
[NARRATOR] This is the tale
of a genius patissier,

00:01:33.561 --> 00:01:35.730 position:21% line:83% align:start
whose dream of making
the world's greatest dessert

00:01:35.863 --> 00:01:37.065 position:30% line:89% align:start
was cut short.

00:01:37.197 --> 00:01:38.800 position:24% line:83% align:start
Now, reincarnated
into another realm

00:01:38.933 --> 00:01:40.300 position:13% line:89% align:start
as the son of a poor noble,

00:01:40.434 --> 00:01:43.705 position:24% line:83% align:start
he pursues a world
full of desserts and smiles!

00:01:44.038 --> 00:01:47.407 position:13% line:83% align:start
A tale that's syrupy sweet,
chock full of yummy treats

00:01:47.542 --> 00:01:50.177 position:33% line:83% align:start
and sprinkled
with bitter darkness.

00:01:50.310 --> 00:01:52.547 position:7% line:89% align:start
A pastry chef, who was reborn,

00:01:52.680 --> 00:01:58.218 position:5% line:83% align:start
and dreams of creating this new
world's very own land of sweets!

00:03:30.845 --> 00:03:33.581 position:13% line:53% align:start
[PAS] After receiving word,
Father moved swiftly.

00:03:33.715 --> 00:03:36.483 position:21% line:53% align:start
We temporarily closed
off the two smaller towns.

00:03:36.617 --> 00:03:38.251 position:35% line:53% align:start
He ordered
their wells filled in,

00:03:38.385 --> 00:03:40.922 position:27% line:53% align:start
and their fields
and homesteads stripped bare.

00:03:41.556 --> 00:03:44.291 position:19% line:53% align:start
Those displaced people
are now hiding out here.

00:03:44.525 --> 00:03:46.894 position:7% line:53% align:start
The goal is to lure the bandits
to us.

00:03:47.028 --> 00:03:49.931 position:21% line:53% align:start
This is all to avoid
a spontaneous battle.

00:03:50.064 --> 00:03:51.364 position:38% line:53% align:start
[FEUILLE]
Boss!

00:03:52.066 --> 00:03:55.169 position:24% line:53% align:start
Well, I rounded up
as many folks as I could.

00:03:55.703 --> 00:03:58.072 position:21% line:53% align:start
[CASSEROLE] How long
do you reckon we can hold out?

00:03:58.206 --> 00:03:59.473 position:38% line:53% align:start
[FEUILLE]
Three days,

00:03:59.607 --> 00:04:01.609 position:19% line:53% align:start
if we ration ourselves
to one meal a day,

00:04:01.743 --> 00:04:04.779 position:5% line:53% align:start
we could probably stretch it out
to seven.

00:04:07.582 --> 00:04:09.150 position:21% line:59% align:start
[indistinct chatter]

00:04:09.282 --> 00:04:10.918 position:10% line:59% align:start
[PAS] We're short on forces.

00:04:11.052 --> 00:04:14.055 position:27% line:53% align:start
Aside from Father
and his retainers Feuille,

00:04:14.188 --> 00:04:15.690 position:19% line:59% align:start
Cointreau, and Glacage,

00:04:15.823 --> 00:04:18.526 position:21% line:53% align:start
we don't have enough
fighting power.

00:04:18.960 --> 00:04:22.730 position:5% line:53% align:start
With these farmers for soldiers,
our side's inferior.

00:04:22.864 --> 00:04:25.600 position:24% line:53% align:start
Father and Feuille
have to know that too.

00:04:25.733 --> 00:04:29.369 position:13% line:53% align:start
-We need a solid strategy.
-[MARC] My Lord Pas!

00:04:29.504 --> 00:04:30.738 position:30% line:59% align:start
Marc and Lumi!

00:04:30.872 --> 00:04:32.640 position:27% line:53% align:start
[MARC] We're here
to fulfill your command!

00:04:32.774 --> 00:04:36.077 position:10% line:53% align:start
My Lord, why, aren't we your
dutiful lieutenants after all?

00:04:36.210 --> 00:04:37.645 position:44% line:53% align:start
[PAS]
My lef-tenants?

00:04:37.779 --> 00:04:39.747 position:16% line:53% align:start
Our fathers are retainers
to this land's suzerain,

00:04:39.881 --> 00:04:41.048 position:27% line:59% align:start
isn't that right?

00:04:41.182 --> 00:04:42.950 position:24% line:53% align:start
Then you must know
that would make us the retainers

00:04:43.084 --> 00:04:45.418 position:21% line:53% align:start
to its next suzerain
and that so happens to be you,

00:04:45.553 --> 00:04:47.688 position:21% line:53% align:start
-if I'm not mistaken?
-[Pas sigh]

00:04:47.822 --> 00:04:50.625 position:16% line:53% align:start
Hearing you two call me,
"My Lord," makes my skin crawl.

00:04:50.758 --> 00:04:53.161 position:24% line:53% align:start
We're old friends,
so why don't you knock it off.

00:04:53.293 --> 00:04:54.361 position:21% line:59% align:start
[Lumi and Marc laugh]

00:04:55.196 --> 00:04:57.565 position:13% line:53% align:start
[PAS] Normally, around this
time, I'd be playing with them

00:04:57.698 --> 00:04:58.933 position:24% line:59% align:start
and the other kids.

00:05:00.268 --> 00:05:01.836 position:21% line:59% align:start
Pas, something wrong?

00:05:01.969 --> 00:05:04.839 position:24% line:53% align:start
Can I ask you guys
to do me a huge favor?

00:05:04.972 --> 00:05:06.707 position:24% line:59% align:start
Sure, you name it!

00:05:06.841 --> 00:05:08.976 position:21% line:53% align:start
Think you can gather
some rocks for me?

00:05:09.110 --> 00:05:10.578 position:41% line:53% align:start
-Rocks?
-Yeah,

00:05:10.711 --> 00:05:12.713 position:21% line:53% align:start
they don't have to be
anything all that special,

00:05:12.847 --> 00:05:14.314 position:24% line:53% align:start
just the right size
for throwing.

00:05:14.447 --> 00:05:15.683 position:41% line:53% align:start
[LUMI]
Roger that.

00:05:15.817 --> 00:05:17.350 position:44% line:53% align:start
[PAS]
Listen to me,

00:05:17.484 --> 00:05:19.153 position:19% line:53% align:start
the bandits are already
within the fief's boundaries.

00:05:19.287 --> 00:05:21.421 position:16% line:53% align:start
So, if you hear something
making noise in the distance

00:05:21.556 --> 00:05:23.758 position:19% line:53% align:start
or see something weird,
don't investigate it,

00:05:23.891 --> 00:05:25.660 position:10% line:53% align:start
just get straight to safety,
okay?

00:05:25.793 --> 00:05:27.528 position:33% line:53% align:start
[LUMI, MARC]
As you command, Lord Pastry!

00:05:27.662 --> 00:05:30.330 position:21% line:53% align:start
I thought I told you,
no more noble treatment!

00:05:31.666 --> 00:05:33.868 position:50% line:59% align:start
âª

00:05:35.870 --> 00:05:37.905 position:33% line:53% align:start
[Marc groans]
There goes my back!

00:05:38.039 --> 00:05:39.807 position:30% line:53% align:start
You sound like
such an old geezer!

00:05:39.941 --> 00:05:42.777 position:19% line:53% align:start
Aw, shut up, you. I bet
we've already done ten laps

00:05:42.910 --> 00:05:44.477 position:24% line:53% align:start
around the village
at this point.

00:05:44.612 --> 00:05:46.080 position:16% line:59% align:start
Oh, yeah, that reminds me

00:05:46.214 --> 00:05:48.249 position:13% line:53% align:start
what kind of magic did Pas
end up getting by the way?

00:05:48.381 --> 00:05:49.884 position:33% line:59% align:start
I don't know,

00:05:50.017 --> 00:05:52.320 position:16% line:53% align:start
he's refusing to tell me
while he's still in training.

00:05:52.452 --> 00:05:54.021 position:19% line:53% align:start
Well, he's so darn good
at everything.

00:05:54.155 --> 00:05:56.624 position:7% line:53% align:start
He should be even further ahead
of you by now, huh?

00:05:56.757 --> 00:05:58.358 position:7% line:59% align:start
What do you mean by that, huh?

00:05:58.491 --> 00:06:01.428 position:7% line:53% align:start
We both know I'm still way more
useful than him in a brawl!

00:06:01.562 --> 00:06:03.598 position:33% line:53% align:start
-Sure, Marc.
-Just you watch me!

00:06:03.731 --> 00:06:06.567 position:7% line:53% align:start
I'll pound those lousy bandits
down...

00:06:07.301 --> 00:06:09.369 position:10% line:59% align:start
Hey, did you hear something?

00:06:09.937 --> 00:06:11.371 position:33% line:53% align:start
Your ears are
pretty much worthless,

00:06:11.505 --> 00:06:13.440 position:16% line:53% align:start
so it's probably nothing
to worry about.

00:06:13.574 --> 00:06:14.909 position:33% line:59% align:start
[Marc shoosh]

00:06:15.442 --> 00:06:17.578 position:35% line:59% align:start
[Marc look]

00:06:21.749 --> 00:06:24.185 position:30% line:53% align:start
-[Marc scared]
-Oh, crap.

00:06:24.318 --> 00:06:26.821 position:50% line:59% align:start
âª

00:06:31.025 --> 00:06:34.095 position:30% line:53% align:start
Hey! Look out!
The bandits are almost here!

00:06:34.228 --> 00:06:35.596 position:13% line:59% align:start
They're here! We saw them!

00:06:35.730 --> 00:06:38.465 position:19% line:53% align:start
Quickly! Close the gate
and draw back the bridge!

00:06:38.599 --> 00:06:41.068 position:21% line:53% align:start
Don't let the bandits
get inside!

00:06:41.202 --> 00:06:42.303 position:41% line:53% align:start
[Marc]
Dad!

00:06:42.435 --> 00:06:45.006 position:5% line:59% align:start
Both of you, stay with Lord Pas.

00:06:45.139 --> 00:06:46.073 position:33% line:53% align:start
[MARC, LUMI]
Sir!

00:06:47.875 --> 00:06:49.644 position:24% line:53% align:start
Please, go and find
all of the little kids

00:06:49.777 --> 00:06:51.646 position:24% line:53% align:start
and get them safely
inside at once, Mother!

00:06:51.779 --> 00:06:53.514 position:33% line:53% align:start
[VILLAGER 1]
No, it's true then?

00:06:53.648 --> 00:06:54.916 position:19% line:59% align:start
They're coming for us?

00:06:55.049 --> 00:06:56.150 position:33% line:53% align:start
[VILLAGER 2]
You really think we'll be enough

00:06:56.284 --> 00:06:57.518 position:33% line:59% align:start
to stop them?

00:06:58.019 --> 00:07:00.187 position:38% line:53% align:start
[FEUILLE]
Don't dare give up yet!

00:07:01.923 --> 00:07:03.157 position:33% line:53% align:start
[VILLAGER 3]
Let's hear him out!

00:07:03.291 --> 00:07:04.959 position:33% line:53% align:start
[VILLAGER 4]
Please be quiet, everyone!

00:07:05.092 --> 00:07:06.527 position:16% line:59% align:start
Listen to me, everybody!

00:07:06.661 --> 00:07:09.330 position:10% line:53% align:start
If the bandits make it here,
men will die,

00:07:09.462 --> 00:07:12.733 position:16% line:53% align:start
your food will be taken,
and your homes burned down!

00:07:13.034 --> 00:07:15.202 position:38% line:53% align:start
I refuse
to ever let that happen here!

00:07:15.336 --> 00:07:17.772 position:41% line:53% align:start
And so,
I ask for your resolve as well!

00:07:18.039 --> 00:07:20.975 position:16% line:53% align:start
Those who wish to protect
their families, join me now!

00:07:21.108 --> 00:07:24.245 position:7% line:53% align:start
We can drive these bandits back
if we work together!

00:07:24.378 --> 00:07:27.148 position:16% line:53% align:start
There's not one man here
I believe to be a coward.

00:07:27.281 --> 00:07:31.953 position:13% line:53% align:start
I hope you share my faith!
Are you all ready for this?

00:07:33.988 --> 00:07:35.756 position:44% line:53% align:start
[PAS]
That's the father I know!

00:07:35.890 --> 00:07:39.492 position:10% line:53% align:start
The villagers who felt afraid
are all riled up! He did it!

00:07:42.330 --> 00:07:43.931 position:5% line:59% align:start
The sun will be setting shortly.

00:07:44.065 --> 00:07:46.233 position:21% line:53% align:start
The bandits will come
when night falls.

00:07:46.367 --> 00:07:47.535 position:21% line:59% align:start
Show me your spirit!

00:07:47.668 --> 00:07:49.503 position:16% line:53% align:start
[Villagers ready to fight
cheers]

00:07:49.637 --> 00:07:51.205 position:35% line:53% align:start
Cointreau,
head to the western canal.

00:07:51.339 --> 00:07:52.974 position:44% line:59% align:start
Sir!

00:07:53.107 --> 00:07:55.076 position:7% line:53% align:start
Glacage, you need to hurry over
to the east-to-center region.

00:07:55.209 --> 00:07:56.644 position:21% line:59% align:start
I'll handle it, sir.

00:07:56.777 --> 00:07:58.646 position:24% line:53% align:start
-Everyone with me!
-[Villagers ready and cheering]

00:07:58.779 --> 00:08:00.147 position:35% line:59% align:start
Wait, boss.

00:08:00.281 --> 00:08:01.649 position:21% line:53% align:start
The bandits would be
at a serious disadvantage

00:08:01.782 --> 00:08:02.984 position:33% line:59% align:start
in the dark.

00:08:03.117 --> 00:08:04.919 position:30% line:53% align:start
They don't know
the area like we do.

00:08:05.052 --> 00:08:06.854 position:30% line:53% align:start
Don't you think
there's still a small chance

00:08:06.988 --> 00:08:08.923 position:21% line:53% align:start
that they might wait
until the morning?

00:08:09.590 --> 00:08:10.958 position:35% line:59% align:start
They won't,

00:08:11.092 --> 00:08:12.460 position:21% line:53% align:start
I suspect they failed
to replenish their food

00:08:12.593 --> 00:08:14.028 position:21% line:53% align:start
and their provisions
have run low.

00:08:14.161 --> 00:08:16.097 position:5% line:53% align:start
Last year's frost will have left
our neighboring fiefs

00:08:16.230 --> 00:08:17.965 position:24% line:53% align:start
with damaged fields
and poor crop yields,

00:08:18.099 --> 00:08:19.767 position:7% line:59% align:start
so they won't find much there.

00:08:19.900 --> 00:08:22.570 position:7% line:53% align:start
I think they'll want to strike
as soon as possible

00:08:22.703 --> 00:08:23.904 position:10% line:59% align:start
and they'll attack at night,

00:08:24.038 --> 00:08:25.706 position:33% line:53% align:start
even if it is
to their disadvantage.

00:08:25.840 --> 00:08:27.408 position:24% line:53% align:start
You can't say that
for sure though.

00:08:27.541 --> 00:08:29.877 position:13% line:53% align:start
If you're wrong and we keep
our men up all night long

00:08:30.011 --> 00:08:32.079 position:24% line:53% align:start
they won't be ready
for a battle.

00:08:32.213 --> 00:08:33.481 position:24% line:59% align:start
Pas, your thoughts?

00:08:34.081 --> 00:08:35.883 position:5% line:59% align:start
There's too much we don't know.

00:08:36.183 --> 00:08:38.753 position:27% line:53% align:start
Ideally, I think
we need to find out, in detail,

00:08:38.886 --> 00:08:41.722 position:16% line:53% align:start
the extent of the enemy's
supplies and fighting power.

00:08:41.856 --> 00:08:43.024 position:24% line:59% align:start
[Casserole agrees]

00:08:43.157 --> 00:08:44.859 position:44% line:53% align:start
[PAS]
It's the same with baking.

00:08:44.992 --> 00:08:46.961 position:13% line:53% align:start
Before you start, you have
to have an accurate measure

00:08:47.094 --> 00:08:48.896 position:21% line:53% align:start
of what you will need
in terms of ingredients,

00:08:49.030 --> 00:08:51.966 position:19% line:53% align:start
time, and temperature,
all prepped beforehand.

00:08:52.099 --> 00:08:55.136 position:13% line:53% align:start
Early on, when I was making
my first chocolate gÃ¢teau--

00:08:55.269 --> 00:08:58.439 position:13% line:53% align:start
No, stop that! You've got
bigger things to focus on!

00:08:58.572 --> 00:09:00.074 position:35% line:53% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
Let's go.

00:09:00.207 --> 00:09:03.110 position:7% line:53% align:start
-[PAS] What're you going to do?
-Armed reconnaissance.

00:09:03.677 --> 00:09:05.279 position:5% line:59% align:start
Feuille, you're coming with me.

00:09:05.413 --> 00:09:08.682 position:10% line:53% align:start
It's still early enough that
we can probably hit them first.

00:09:08.816 --> 00:09:12.119 position:35% line:53% align:start
Good grief.
You're such a taskmaster, boss.

00:09:12.319 --> 00:09:15.423 position:5% line:53% align:start
[CASSEROLE] Pas, I'm leaving you
in charge in my absence, son.

00:09:15.556 --> 00:09:16.857 position:38% line:59% align:start
Yes, sir!

00:09:19.026 --> 00:09:21.729 position:21% line:53% align:start
[CASSEROLE] We'll hit
the bandits hard and withdraw.

00:09:21.862 --> 00:09:24.298 position:7% line:53% align:start
Feuille and I will take a long,
roundabout route

00:09:24.432 --> 00:09:26.167 position:5% line:59% align:start
and then return from the North.

00:09:26.300 --> 00:09:27.802 position:35% line:59% align:start
Take care!

00:09:27.935 --> 00:09:30.104 position:7% line:53% align:start
[PAS] Before they make it back,
I'll use my own judgement

00:09:30.237 --> 00:09:32.173 position:33% line:53% align:start
to figure out
what I can do to help.

00:09:33.107 --> 00:09:35.976 position:33% line:53% align:start
Marc, listen.
I need you to pass this message

00:09:36.110 --> 00:09:38.179 position:33% line:53% align:start
to Cointreau
at the western canal.

00:09:38.312 --> 00:09:41.082 position:13% line:53% align:start
"Flaming arrows will signal
the enemy's approach."

00:09:41.415 --> 00:09:42.817 position:21% line:59% align:start
Lumi, go tell Glacage

00:09:42.950 --> 00:09:45.252 position:24% line:53% align:start
to start preparing
the flaming arrows at once.

00:09:46.053 --> 00:09:48.055 position:21% line:53% align:start
[PAS] While my father
and Feuille are gone,

00:09:48.189 --> 00:09:51.425 position:10% line:53% align:start
the very second you hear even
the faintest sound of hoofbeats,

00:09:51.560 --> 00:09:55.129 position:5% line:53% align:start
tell them to shoot their arrows
in the direction of the sound.

00:09:55.262 --> 00:09:56.565 position:27% line:59% align:start
You sure, though?

00:09:56.697 --> 00:09:59.200 position:7% line:53% align:start
What if the arrows accidentally
hit His Lordship as well?

00:09:59.333 --> 00:10:01.168 position:24% line:53% align:start
You think my father
would let himself get hit

00:10:01.302 --> 00:10:03.637 position:27% line:53% align:start
by a stray arrow
fired from that far away?

00:10:03.771 --> 00:10:04.972 position:33% line:59% align:start
[Marc laughs]

00:10:05.106 --> 00:10:06.575 position:44% line:53% align:start
Yeah,
that's pretty hard to imagine!

00:10:06.707 --> 00:10:10.545 position:10% line:53% align:start
I mean, he once did something
I'd never seen before.

00:10:11.112 --> 00:10:13.582 position:16% line:53% align:start
He dodged a falling rock
by instinct!

00:10:13.714 --> 00:10:16.851 position:7% line:53% align:start
Yeah, he really took us to task
after we pulled that prank.

00:10:16.984 --> 00:10:19.620 position:19% line:53% align:start
He was so mad, he even
went after your dad for it!

00:10:19.753 --> 00:10:21.155 position:21% line:59% align:start
[Marc and Lumi laugh]

00:10:21.288 --> 00:10:22.524 position:33% line:59% align:start
[Pas amused]

00:10:22.656 --> 00:10:23.891 position:10% line:53% align:start
No matter how well they know
the land,

00:10:24.024 --> 00:10:25.793 position:21% line:53% align:start
they could still lose
their way home,

00:10:25.926 --> 00:10:28.129 position:24% line:53% align:start
especially at night
with bandits after them.

00:10:28.262 --> 00:10:30.731 position:13% line:53% align:start
So, I'm hoping those arrows
help guide them home.

00:10:30.865 --> 00:10:33.467 position:13% line:53% align:start
But, uh, can't he teleport
with magic?

00:10:33.602 --> 00:10:36.237 position:19% line:53% align:start
His teleportation spell
has a weight limit.

00:10:36.370 --> 00:10:38.272 position:16% line:53% align:start
It would be hard for him
to use it on both of them

00:10:38.405 --> 00:10:41.675 position:10% line:53% align:start
-and the horses all at once.
-Never knew about that.

00:10:41.809 --> 00:10:43.077 position:33% line:53% align:start
-That's wild!
-All right!

00:10:43.210 --> 00:10:45.514 position:21% line:53% align:start
-Now, to your tasks!
-[Marc and Lumi] Got it!

00:10:45.646 --> 00:10:47.348 position:16% line:59% align:start
[Marc and Lumi take off]

00:10:48.983 --> 00:10:50.251 position:38% line:53% align:start
[GIRL 1]
I'm so scared!

00:10:50.484 --> 00:10:52.086 position:7% line:53% align:start
[MARIE] What's going to happen
to the village?

00:10:52.219 --> 00:10:54.523 position:24% line:53% align:start
It'll be all right.
Don't be too scared, okay?

00:10:54.755 --> 00:10:57.758 position:10% line:53% align:start
My daddy and all your daddies
will keep us safe from harm.

00:10:57.892 --> 00:10:59.894 position:19% line:53% align:start
They won't let anything
bad happen!

00:11:00.027 --> 00:11:03.697 position:21% line:53% align:start
We can count on them.
Now, you go inside too, Josie.

00:11:03.831 --> 00:11:05.799 position:41% line:53% align:start
[JOSIE]
Yes. Let's go.

00:11:06.233 --> 00:11:07.368 position:30% line:59% align:start
Please, Pas...

00:11:09.403 --> 00:11:11.805 position:19% line:53% align:start
-Be careful out there.
-Ma'am!

00:11:12.507 --> 00:11:14.041 position:19% line:53% align:start
[PAS] I thought sweets
were the only thing

00:11:14.175 --> 00:11:16.043 position:19% line:53% align:start
I'd ever have to worry
much about.

00:11:16.443 --> 00:11:19.780 position:27% line:53% align:start
But in this world
if I don't protect my territory,

00:11:19.914 --> 00:11:23.150 position:16% line:53% align:start
my dream won't come true
so I'll do what I must do!

00:11:23.284 --> 00:11:26.954 position:10% line:53% align:start
To take care of these people
and make them smile.

00:11:27.221 --> 00:11:28.322 position:27% line:59% align:start
That's my dream.

00:11:28.756 --> 00:11:31.458 position:10% line:53% align:start
That's what a land of sweets
means!

00:11:33.794 --> 00:11:35.262 position:27% line:59% align:start
What Father wants

00:11:35.396 --> 00:11:37.464 position:19% line:53% align:start
is to hurry up and get
the battle over with tonight,

00:11:37.599 --> 00:11:40.334 position:21% line:53% align:start
even if he, himself,
has to be the bait.

00:11:41.168 --> 00:11:44.738 position:21% line:53% align:start
Pas, I'm leaving you
in charge in my absence.

00:11:47.208 --> 00:11:49.877 position:27% line:53% align:start
Prepare yourself
to fight off these bandits!

00:11:50.010 --> 00:11:51.212 position:21% line:59% align:start
[indistinct chatter]

00:11:51.345 --> 00:11:54.415 position:16% line:53% align:start
Gather all the kids here!
I have a plan!

00:12:17.071 --> 00:12:19.974 position:30% line:53% align:start
Found 'em, boss
and I've got bad news.

00:12:20.274 --> 00:12:21.509 position:27% line:59% align:start
These "bandits."

00:12:22.343 --> 00:12:24.945 position:21% line:53% align:start
At least a few appear
to be trained cavalrymen.

00:12:25.446 --> 00:12:29.250 position:16% line:53% align:start
They've got five horses,
strong ones, in good shape,

00:12:29.383 --> 00:12:32.086 position:13% line:53% align:start
and it looks like they know
how to ride 'em too.

00:12:32.219 --> 00:12:33.854 position:35% line:53% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
How many men, all told?

00:12:33.988 --> 00:12:37.258 position:5% line:59% align:start
Fifty, sixty, no about seventy.

00:12:37.391 --> 00:12:39.860 position:19% line:53% align:start
It seems unlikely that
they were driven to banditry

00:12:39.994 --> 00:12:41.895 position:24% line:59% align:start
out of desperation.

00:12:42.530 --> 00:12:44.031 position:33% line:59% align:start
My guess is,

00:12:44.164 --> 00:12:46.233 position:21% line:53% align:start
we're contending with
an experienced gang of raiders.

00:12:46.367 --> 00:12:47.569 position:30% line:59% align:start
That's not all.

00:12:47.702 --> 00:12:49.937 position:21% line:53% align:start
They've got captives
tied up in their camp, too.

00:12:50.572 --> 00:12:53.474 position:24% line:53% align:start
Probably villagers
they kidnapped for slave labor.

00:12:54.475 --> 00:12:57.044 position:13% line:53% align:start
I swear, I won't allow them
to do that to anyone

00:12:57.177 --> 00:13:00.281 position:21% line:53% align:start
living in our lands!
Do not fall behind, Feuille.

00:13:00.414 --> 00:13:02.283 position:27% line:53% align:start
Who do you think
you're talking to?

00:13:02.416 --> 00:13:04.218 position:21% line:53% align:start
You'd better keep up
the pace yourself

00:13:04.351 --> 00:13:06.987 position:7% line:53% align:start
if you don't feel like catching
an arrow in the butt, Boss!

00:13:07.121 --> 00:13:08.222 position:24% line:59% align:start
[Casserole amused]

00:13:13.294 --> 00:13:15.796 position:10% line:53% align:start
We're back, chief. Looks like
the surrounding villages

00:13:15.929 --> 00:13:17.264 position:16% line:59% align:start
have all been abandoned.

00:13:17.398 --> 00:13:19.500 position:10% line:53% align:start
And they filled in the wells
when they left.

00:13:19.634 --> 00:13:20.735 position:33% line:59% align:start
[Helm amused]

00:13:20.868 --> 00:13:22.136 position:27% line:59% align:start
Yeah, I figured.

00:13:22.269 --> 00:13:23.772 position:16% line:59% align:start
They heard we were coming

00:13:23.904 --> 00:13:26.940 position:13% line:53% align:start
and decided to concentrate
their defenses in one place.

00:13:27.074 --> 00:13:29.176 position:24% line:59% align:start
Well, that's fine.

00:13:29.476 --> 00:13:30.645 position:27% line:59% align:start
The sun is down.

00:13:31.278 --> 00:13:33.314 position:27% line:53% align:start
-Let's head out.
-[Bandit 2C and 2D] Right!

00:13:39.654 --> 00:13:41.422 position:27% line:59% align:start
[Feuille attack]

00:13:43.223 --> 00:13:45.159 position:24% line:59% align:start
[Bandit 2F sliced]

00:13:46.093 --> 00:13:48.329 position:7% line:59% align:start
They're soldiers from Morteln?

00:13:48.730 --> 00:13:49.930 position:35% line:59% align:start
[Helm gasp]

00:13:53.500 --> 00:13:55.670 position:19% line:53% align:start
[HELM] They're focusing
on cutting through the camp,

00:13:55.804 --> 00:13:57.772 position:5% line:59% align:start
not on taking out our fighters.

00:13:58.339 --> 00:14:01.442 position:19% line:53% align:start
These guys know a thing
or two about cavalry tactics.

00:14:02.042 --> 00:14:03.778 position:7% line:59% align:start
They got to be trained riders!

00:14:03.911 --> 00:14:05.145 position:19% line:59% align:start
Brace yourselves, boys,

00:14:05.279 --> 00:14:07.181 position:21% line:53% align:start
they're about to make
another pass!

00:14:07.816 --> 00:14:10.117 position:38% line:59% align:start
[groans]

00:14:10.918 --> 00:14:13.655 position:16% line:53% align:start
Hey! Don't stand in front
of their horses, you morons!

00:14:14.088 --> 00:14:15.923 position:16% line:53% align:start
You're just going to get
trampled!

00:14:16.056 --> 00:14:18.992 position:24% line:53% align:start
Their leader knows
the right orders to give.

00:14:19.661 --> 00:14:22.329 position:13% line:53% align:start
Then we won't get much done
with another charge.

00:14:24.064 --> 00:14:26.033 position:7% line:53% align:start
We got to run before these guys
overwhelm us

00:14:26.166 --> 00:14:27.535 position:16% line:59% align:start
with their numbers, boss!

00:14:27.669 --> 00:14:30.839 position:13% line:53% align:start
All right, let's head back
and muster our defenses!

00:14:30.971 --> 00:14:32.139 position:13% line:59% align:start
[Bandits fired up chasing]

00:14:32.272 --> 00:14:34.007 position:35% line:53% align:start
[BANDIT 2L]
Don't let 'em escape!

00:14:34.141 --> 00:14:35.309 position:35% line:53% align:start
[BANDIT 2M]
Don't let 'em get back--!

00:14:35.442 --> 00:14:37.144 position:41% line:53% align:start
[HELM]
Don't run off, you idiots!

00:14:37.277 --> 00:14:40.314 position:21% line:59% align:start
[indistinct chatter]

00:14:40.447 --> 00:14:41.583 position:38% line:59% align:start
Amateurs!

00:14:43.317 --> 00:14:45.219 position:35% line:53% align:start
Looks like
they all took the bait, Boss.

00:14:45.352 --> 00:14:47.354 position:30% line:53% align:start
Let's get back
to the village safely!

00:14:52.459 --> 00:14:55.195 position:21% line:53% align:start
Um, something wrong,
Sir Glacage?

00:15:01.201 --> 00:15:04.171 position:27% line:53% align:start
-The fire arrows.
-Yes, right away, sir!

00:15:16.049 --> 00:15:18.018 position:19% line:59% align:start
Godspeed you, my lord.

00:15:20.822 --> 00:15:24.659 position:7% line:53% align:start
The signal! Everyone get ready,
the bandits are on their way!

00:15:28.295 --> 00:15:30.832 position:33% line:53% align:start
A fire arrow
and it came from the village!

00:15:30.964 --> 00:15:32.534 position:24% line:59% align:start
That has to be Pas.

00:15:32.667 --> 00:15:35.570 position:21% line:53% align:start
He's using the arrows
to guide us back home

00:15:35.703 --> 00:15:37.304 position:13% line:53% align:start
and if he's willing to use
tactics

00:15:37.438 --> 00:15:40.040 position:24% line:53% align:start
that will give away
the location of the village,

00:15:40.174 --> 00:15:42.075 position:5% line:59% align:start
I'll bet he's set up an ambush!

00:15:42.877 --> 00:15:45.613 position:5% line:53% align:start
They'll ruin the fields if we go
around to the east side.

00:15:45.747 --> 00:15:47.448 position:19% line:53% align:start
Will have to break off
to the west.

00:15:47.582 --> 00:15:50.685 position:19% line:53% align:start
I guess we'll find out
what he's planned. Let's go!

00:15:52.720 --> 00:15:54.656 position:33% line:53% align:start
[VILLAGER 5]
Lord Pas! Emergency!

00:15:54.789 --> 00:15:56.356 position:13% line:59% align:start
[Villager 5 running effort]

00:15:56.490 --> 00:15:59.460 position:10% line:53% align:start
His Lordship and Sir Feuille
are being pursued by bandits!

00:15:59.594 --> 00:16:01.896 position:27% line:53% align:start
-And the arrows?
-We've already loosed two.

00:16:02.029 --> 00:16:05.365 position:7% line:53% align:start
They seem to be circling around
the west side of the village.

00:16:05.499 --> 00:16:06.500 position:38% line:59% align:start
[Pas nod]

00:16:07.201 --> 00:16:08.603 position:44% line:53% align:start
[PAS]
Prepare to fight back!

00:16:08.736 --> 00:16:11.271 position:50% line:59% align:start
âª

00:16:15.075 --> 00:16:17.211 position:21% line:59% align:start
[indistinct chatter]

00:16:17.579 --> 00:16:20.414 position:33% line:53% align:start
We'll butcher
every last one of you!

00:16:20.882 --> 00:16:22.316 position:21% line:59% align:start
Time for that detour!

00:16:24.384 --> 00:16:28.255 position:50% line:59% align:start
âª

00:16:33.728 --> 00:16:35.462 position:35% line:59% align:start
Now, fire!

00:16:38.432 --> 00:16:42.035 position:7% line:59% align:start
[screams of pain being pelted]

00:16:44.338 --> 00:16:46.608 position:38% line:53% align:start
Damn it,
we ran right into their trap!

00:16:47.174 --> 00:16:48.408 position:41% line:59% align:start
Ready!

00:16:50.945 --> 00:16:54.549 position:33% line:53% align:start
-Next volley!
-[pelted on fire]

00:16:57.317 --> 00:17:01.021 position:24% line:53% align:start
-[PAS] And another!
-[Marc laugh]

00:17:01.154 --> 00:17:02.389 position:24% line:59% align:start
Who'd have thought?

00:17:02.524 --> 00:17:04.458 position:35% line:53% align:start
Good thing
we play with slings so much!

00:17:05.860 --> 00:17:07.929 position:10% line:53% align:start
[PAS] When Father and Feuille
are on their way back

00:17:08.061 --> 00:17:09.463 position:7% line:59% align:start
from attacking the bandit camp

00:17:09.597 --> 00:17:12.800 position:24% line:53% align:start
they'll break west
to avoid trampling the fields.

00:17:13.200 --> 00:17:15.035 position:30% line:53% align:start
And most likely
the bandits chasing them

00:17:15.168 --> 00:17:17.271 position:27% line:53% align:start
will have to fall
into a straight line.

00:17:17.404 --> 00:17:20.575 position:19% line:53% align:start
The flank of that line
will be their weak point.

00:17:21.308 --> 00:17:23.343 position:33% line:53% align:start
That's where
we'll aim our attack.

00:17:23.578 --> 00:17:26.179 position:10% line:53% align:start
But, wait, is it safe to have
our kids doing this?

00:17:26.313 --> 00:17:28.448 position:7% line:53% align:start
Well, it's not like any of you
grown-ups remember

00:17:28.583 --> 00:17:30.652 position:10% line:53% align:start
how to properly use a sling,
right?

00:17:30.785 --> 00:17:32.020 position:21% line:59% align:start
[indistinct chatter]

00:17:32.152 --> 00:17:34.154 position:24% line:53% align:start
And we all use them
for fun every day!

00:17:34.288 --> 00:17:35.557 position:16% line:59% align:start
Yeah, you tell 'em, Lumi!

00:17:35.690 --> 00:17:37.959 position:27% line:53% align:start
We may be young,
but we're strong, too!

00:17:38.091 --> 00:17:40.294 position:5% line:53% align:start
Now, don't get full of yourself,
boy.

00:17:40.795 --> 00:17:42.797 position:16% line:59% align:start
It's only a small ambush.

00:17:42.931 --> 00:17:45.432 position:13% line:53% align:start
However, if we can disrupt
their formation

00:17:45.567 --> 00:17:47.401 position:21% line:53% align:start
and throw their force
into disarray,

00:17:47.535 --> 00:17:50.805 position:7% line:53% align:start
Father and Feuille will be able
to move around more freely.

00:17:50.939 --> 00:17:53.708 position:21% line:59% align:start
[indistinct chatter]

00:17:53.841 --> 00:17:56.811 position:5% line:53% align:start
If we can have the children help
out with our defense early on,

00:17:56.945 --> 00:17:59.581 position:19% line:53% align:start
they won't have as much
of an advantage in numbers.

00:18:00.548 --> 00:18:03.751 position:10% line:53% align:start
And once they cross the canal
the children will fall back

00:18:03.885 --> 00:18:06.754 position:19% line:53% align:start
and the village militia
will meet the enemy.

00:18:08.088 --> 00:18:09.489 position:33% line:53% align:start
[VILLAGER 6]
Understood.

00:18:09.624 --> 00:18:12.860 position:16% line:53% align:start
His Lordship told us all
to protect the village together.

00:18:13.661 --> 00:18:16.064 position:24% line:53% align:start
Let's all carry out
Lord Pas' defense plan!

00:18:16.196 --> 00:18:17.665 position:44% line:53% align:start
[ALL]
Yeah!

00:18:17.799 --> 00:18:21.903 position:5% line:53% align:start
Nice, let's show those old farts
what we can do! [laugh]

00:18:22.036 --> 00:18:25.640 position:10% line:53% align:start
Lumi, I'd really feel better
if you sat this one out,

00:18:25.773 --> 00:18:28.442 position:10% line:53% align:start
considering how you're a girl
and everything.

00:18:28.576 --> 00:18:31.478 position:19% line:53% align:start
So, what if I'm a girl?
I'm your retainer!

00:18:31.846 --> 00:18:34.515 position:13% line:53% align:start
Not to mention I'm probably
the best slinger here.

00:18:34.649 --> 00:18:38.052 position:27% line:53% align:start
Yeah, good point.
Thanks for setting me straight.

00:18:38.185 --> 00:18:40.287 position:10% line:59% align:start
I'm not sure if I can do it.

00:18:44.659 --> 00:18:47.862 position:35% line:53% align:start
-Lord Pas.
-I promise you'll do fine, guys.

00:18:47.996 --> 00:18:50.865 position:13% line:53% align:start
Just play with your slings,
like any other day.

00:18:50.999 --> 00:18:52.165 position:41% line:53% align:start
[BOYS]
Yes, sir!

00:18:53.166 --> 00:18:56.738 position:13% line:53% align:start
[PAS] I swear. I won't let
any of these children get hurt!

00:18:56.871 --> 00:18:59.707 position:27% line:53% align:start
-Slings, release!
-[pelted by flaming rocks]

00:19:01.609 --> 00:19:03.578 position:38% line:53% align:start
[FEUILLE]
Whoa! Nice work, kid!

00:19:03.711 --> 00:19:05.445 position:35% line:53% align:start
[CASSEROLE]
Let's go, Feuille! Keep it up!

00:19:05.580 --> 00:19:07.447 position:38% line:53% align:start
[FEUILLE]
You got it, Boss!

00:19:08.549 --> 00:19:10.985 position:24% line:59% align:start
Stupid brats. Hyah!

00:19:11.119 --> 00:19:13.788 position:30% line:59% align:start
[walla bandits]

00:19:15.623 --> 00:19:17.759 position:21% line:53% align:start
One of 'em is heading
for the wall!

00:19:17.992 --> 00:19:19.627 position:33% line:59% align:start
Slings ready!

00:19:19.761 --> 00:19:24.197 position:33% line:53% align:start
-[Helm block]
-No more games!

00:19:24.331 --> 00:19:25.667 position:33% line:59% align:start
[Pas scoffs]

00:19:34.408 --> 00:19:37.310 position:35% line:53% align:start
[BANDIT 2E]
This way! Follow the chief!

00:19:38.012 --> 00:19:40.882 position:27% line:53% align:start
Everyone look out
the bandits are here!

00:19:43.350 --> 00:19:45.687 position:33% line:53% align:start
[VILLAGER 7]
Lord Pas, run!

00:19:48.221 --> 00:19:50.858 position:19% line:59% align:start
[Helm grabs and pulls]

00:19:53.193 --> 00:19:56.531 position:10% line:59% align:start
[Helm jump over and attacks]

00:20:00.001 --> 00:20:03.838 position:7% line:53% align:start
All right, step up and face me
if you're ready to die!

00:20:04.471 --> 00:20:06.808 position:27% line:59% align:start
[Glacage step up]

00:20:07.407 --> 00:20:08.643 position:33% line:59% align:start
[Helm scoff]

00:20:08.776 --> 00:20:11.211 position:5% line:59% align:start
